INSTALLATION:
1. There is an environment variable KARLA which you should set to your
   local Karla directory.  

2. In order to use
   $(KARLA)/config/sk.tcl, put it somewhere in your path and add the

	#!/usr/local/bin/wish

   to wherever your 'wish' is to be found.  Then, adapt the data base in $KARLA/karla.sko using

	perl -pe "s*/usr/public/Karla-0.5*YOUR_KARLA_DIR*g" $KARLA/karla.sko > $(KARLA)/karla.sko.new

   where YOUR_KARLA_DIR points to your local Karla directory.

3.  Replace $(Karla)/karla.sko with $(Karla)/karla.sko.new

4.  edit $KARLA/config/sk.tcl to point to the right location for your
    FSBox widget. The original statement is

	source /usr/public/tools/TclTk/lib/FSBox.tcl

    and most likely useless in your environment.

A good point to get started is to run sk.tcl and play with it.
Initial documentation is provided in $KARLA/doc/Karla_II.ps